INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0605812A$$, 2027, $$The Joint Light Tactical Vehicle (JLTV) is the cornerstone of protected tactical mobility for the Army and Marine Corps. This RDT&E request is critical, time-sensitive
investment to master the threats of today and tomorrow. Warfighters face a growing danger from Unmanned Aerial Systems (UAS), while the demand for on-board
electrical power for advanced sensors, communication suites, and future weapons has surged. This creates an urgent capability gap. This funding request closes a
capability gap by delivering tangible capabilities with a clear strategic impact.

 The program element supports modernization of the JLTV Family of Vehicles by investigating capability upgrades/insertions, including but not limited to force protection/
 survivability improvements, predictive logistics, platform safety enhancements including operations in extreme environments, trailer integration and technologies to meet
 other emerging operational needs.

 Funding the integration of the priority efforts includes: previously developed Tactical Range Extender (TREE) and the electric Power Export and Expansion Kit (ePEEK)
 as well as development of the hardware needed to bring platforms to autonomy ready status. TREE and ePEEK are a unified, mobile power system that transforms any
 tactical vehicle into a power hub that can provide any High Voltage DC power or AC. It delivers the massive amounts of versatile, exportable electricity needed to run the
 Army's most advanced systems on the move.

 This investment works to make our vehicle platforms "autonomy-ready." It buys the essential power architecture that unlocks the next generation of modernization, from
 autonomous systems and predictive logistics to advanced survivability upgrades. This technology provides the power backbone necessary to integrate drone-killing
 systems directly onto the JLTV. It Increases Warfighter Survivability & Agility: By generating power on the move, it reduces the logistical burden on forces and shrinks
 their acoustic and thermal signatures, making a harder for the enemy to target.

 This funding ensures warfighters have the dominant tactical vehicle needed for the challenges of a complex world.

 FY 2027 Justification:
 The FY 2027 budget funds of $2.749 million will be utilized for the continuation of the development and assessment of emerging technologies to maintain operational
 relevancy. Technologies under consideration include but not limited to autonomy enablers, power generation (Tactical Range Extender Enhanced (TREE), electric
 Power Export and Expansion Kit (ePEEK),signature management, winter tires, Counter Unmanned Aircraft Systems (cUAS) capabilities, and improved force protection.$$, $$The Joint Light Tactical Vehicle (JLTV) is the cornerstone of protected tactical mobility for the Army and Marine Corps. This RDT&E request is critical, time-sensitive
