Description: Funding supports development of new mission-critical Open Mission Systems/Universal Command and Control
Interface (OMS/UCI) features requested by the 30+ operational adopting platforms across the DAF, Department of War and
international partners. Funding also supports experimentation, modeling, integration events, and studies to establish a common
DAF Modular Open Systems Approach (MOSA) approach. This includes leveraging non-traditional industry standards and
government-driven standards, such as the AFRL's Big Iron, and the "Horizontal Integration” approach (formerly known as
Government Avionics Reference Architecture or GARA) effort to streamline integration across multiple architectures and
standards. These efforts use agile methodologies and Development, Security, and Operations (DevSecOps) software practices
to deliver products securely to adopting platforms and enable continuous feedback to improve the standards. Additionally,
funding provides targeted technical exploration and risk reduction with adopting platforms to facilitate their MOSA adoption while
identifying any changes required within the DAF's MOSA standards.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Increase adoptability with USSF/Command, Control, Communications and Battle Management (C3BM) systems to support DAF
Battle Network
- Rapidly respond to emerging technologies, operational weapons systems feature request and adopting platform requirements by
completing 85-95 change requests annually
- Align Open Mission System (OMS) with Agile Mission Suite Government Reference Architecture (AMS GRA), unlocking
additional capabilities for future adopters
- Continue technical maturation of the OMS and UCI standards
- Conduct targeted training to new and existing adopters
- Merge subsystem architectures with open architecture management
- Develop and update open hardware technical standards for government reference architecture implementations
- Define domain-specific data modeling usage for joint interoperability
- Mature MBSE products within open architectures
- Begin planning for adopting Sensor Open Systems Architecture (SOSA) requirements
FY 2027 Plans:
- Craft targeted prototype of open architecture implementation to inform maturation efforts and ease adoption
- Complete 95 change requests in FY27
- Continue technical maturation of the OMS and UCI standards
- Continue to update standards to account for emerging technologies and operational weapon system feature requests
- Support feature requests from deployment of UCI in support of the DAF Battle Network
- Conduct targeted training to new and existing adopters to ease implementation
- Horizontally integrate and rationalize standards with other mission system architecture products

