Remarks

E. Acquisition Strategy
The Acquisition Decision Memorandum (ADM) dated July 8, 2024 recertified the LGM-35A Sentinel program to continue in accordance with Title 10, United States
Code, Section 4376. The Milestone Decision Authority (MDA) rescinded the program's Milestone B approval and the original Acquisition Program Baseline approved
on September 4, 2020. The Air Force shall restructure the LGM-35A Sentinel program prior to MDA approval of a new Milestone B and develop a modified acquisition
strategy that reflects the restructured Sentinel program. Congress has been briefed on the phased Milestone B approach and that entry/exit criteria will be codified 1 Aug
with Milestone B Criteria Set

 The LGM-35A Sentinel program will revalidate program requirements to deliver a full, integrated weapon system capability that meets Air Force Global Strike
 Command's Capability Development Document requirements. Preserve cost, schedule, and performance trade space of the Sentinel ICBM program at and below the
 key systems attribute level. Conduct an integrated baseline review in support of MS B approval to identify major risks in the contractor's performance measurement
 baseline, including scope, schedule, and budget for major suppliers. Update the LGM-35A Sentinel Software Development Plan to include software architecture,



