A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Research Site Support Project ensures the continued operation, maintenance, and modernization of the Rome Research Site infrastructure in Rome, New
York. This site is a strategic asset supporting both the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) and the Defense Finance and Accounting Service (DFAS), enabling
uninterrupted research, innovation, and financial operations essential to national defense. The project provides comprehensive support for all Rome Research Site
properties, buildings, utilities, and services—ensuring a secure, resilient, and fully functional environment for day-to-day mission execution and long-term strategic
objectives.

