Description: This effort will develop a replacement for the current M68 Mine Clearing Line Charge (MICLIC) training round which
has proven to be expensive and difficult to utilize. The M68 trainer is designed to be fired 3 times but repacking the inert line
charge into its "tub" after a firing event is a manpower intensive and time consuming endeavor, which leads to an ineffective
training experience for soldiers. This effort will explore concepts and qualify a solution that provides a realistic training experience
