Title: 3) Aerosol Vapor Chemical Agent Detector (AVCAD)                                                                                 5.592         6.000        3.371
Description: The Aerosol Vapor Chemical Agent Detector (AVCAD) is a system that detects chemical agent aerosol and
vapor consisting of two configurations, Man-Portable and Shipboard Fixed. AVCAD will perform remote alarm warning and
reporting; preventing/mitigating health effects associated with low concentration exposure. AVCAD supports chemical defense
missions, including collective protection, base defense, decontamination, reconnaissance, and surveillance. AVCAD Man-
Portable is a single detector unit that is capable of integration with mobile platforms to include the CBRN Reconnaissance Modular
Mission Payload (CRMMP) effort. AVCAD Shipboard Fixed consists of two detector units, two displays units, sampling lines and
integration hardware that will be integrated onto ships. AVCAD is network capable and supports the services Integrated Layered
Defense (ILD) concept through use of Government communication protocols. AVCAD benefits the warfighter by providing a
sensitive aerosol and vapor chemical detection capability.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete product development, and Systems Engineering. Complete program management and administrative processes and
Other Government Agency (OGA) support for logistics and test evaluation results in support of a Full Rate Production
(FRP) decision.
FY 2027 Plans:
Initiate AVCAD capability expansion to include Pharmaceutical Based Agents (PBA). Modify the contract to include algorithm
development for the PBA, updating logistics products and support of verification testing. Continue program management,
administrative processes and Other Government Agency (OGA) support for logistics and test support.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:



