Title: 4) Chemical and Biological Wearables (CB WEARABLES)                                                                                   -          8.959      10.046
Description: The Chemical and Biological Wearables (CB WEARABLES) program develops and equips joint warfighters with
software capabilities that analyze physiological data collected from wearable sensors and alert potential exposure to CB threats.
These software capabilities integrate into the hardware-focused decision support tools developed under the CB-WEARABLES
– Enhanced Biological Defense (ENBD) program. CB WEARABLES benefits the warfighter by providing commanders with
actionable information to maximize warfighter readiness, performance, and resiliency before, during, and after CB operations.
The program integrated software capabilities transitioned from the Physiological Monitoring Sensor Suite (PM2S) program line
beginning in FY 2023, with full transition of efforts completed in FY 2025.

FY 2026 Plans:
Efforts support advanced experimentation activities with joint warfighters to identify CB defense capability gaps across the
services. As part of a coordinated experimentation campaign, the program will use BA5 to verify, validate, and integrate
physiological monitoring software capabilities into the hardware-focused decision support tools developed under the CB
WEARABLES-ENBD program.
FY 2027 Plans:
Efforts support advanced experimentation activities with joint warfighters to identify CB defense capability gaps across the
services. As part of a coordinated experimentation campaign, the program will use BA5 to verify, validate, and integrate
physiological monitoring software capabilities into the hardware-focused decision support tools developed under the CB
WEARABLES-ENBD program.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Program/project funding transferred from another thrust area. Efforts transitioned from BA4 to BA5 in support of System
Development and Demonstration activities.
Title: 5) Chemical and Biological Wearables - Enhanced Biological Defense (CB WEARABLES-ENBD)                                           24.707      23.899         19.799
Description: The Chemical and Biological Wearables-ENBD (CB WEARABLES-ENBD) effort continues to develop network
interfaces needed to integrate wearable physiological monitoring capabilities directly into service-sponsored decision support
tools and mission command systems. The program benefits the warfighter by enabling the detection and warning of physiological
anomalies that may indicate exposure to biological warfare agents (BWA) and other emerging threats, increasing readiness and
resiliency across the joint force. CB WEARABLES-ENBD will continue to directly interface and integrate wearables with existing
joint force computing environments and directly supports the strategic goals of the CBDP's Enhanced Biological Defense effort.


