Title: 6) Colorimetric Indicator (CIND)                                                                                                          -              -        2.765
Description: The CIND is a low-cost, easy to use, ultra-low size, weight, power, and cost (SWaP C) modular open system
based chemical detector that is widely distributed to the General Forces as an integrated kit for indication of chemical hazards.
CIND will provide detection and classification capabilities for traditional, advanced and or emerging chemical hazards such as
chemical warfare agents (CWA), non-traditional agents (NTA), pharmaceutical-based agents (PBA), riot control agents (RCA),
toxic industrial chemicals (TIC), and toxins in all states of matter (solid, liquid, vapor, aerosol). These capabilities can be deployed
on unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and unmanned ground vehicles (UGVs) for automated threat detection. By integrating
these unmanned capabilities, CIND will strengthen integrated layered defense and provide critical early warning data to inform
Commander's decisions. CIND benefits the warfighter by providing a low-cost, easy to use, higher confidence liquid, solid, and
vapor hazard detection capabilities in a chemical hazard environment; providing an effective and timely tool for multi-domain
decision making in the forward operating environment.

