Title: 16) Chemical Biological Radiological Nuclear Reconnaissance Modular Mission Payload (CRMMP)                                          -             -       39.938
Description: The Chemical Biological Radiological Nuclear Reconnaissance Modular Mission Payload (CRMMP) is designed
to maximize platform agnostic capabilities to enable integration onto current and future manned/unmanned platforms. Nuclear
Biological Chemical Reconnaissance Vehicle Sensor Suite Upgrade (NBCRV SSU) funding is transitioning to CRMMP in FY
2027 to complete development of the Capability Set 2.2 (CS2.2) Low-Rate Initial Production (LRIP) assets onto current and future
manned/unmanned platforms per the updated acquisition strategy. CRMMP will deliver mounted CBRN Reconnaissance and
Surveillance capabilities to increase standoff distance from threats and integrates onto robotic platforms for human machine
integration (HMI). CRMMP benefits the Warfighter by allowing missions ahead of the main body, both reducing risk to the
force and the mission, and enabling Joint Force commanders with decision quality data for timelier situational awareness and
understanding to expedite decision making and ensure freedom of maneuver.

FY 2027 Plans:
Complete chemical and biological sensor and overall modular mission payload (previously NBCRV SSU Capability Set 2.2)
development and integration efforts of CRMMP LRIP assets. Continue sensor level developmental and operational testing and
initiate system level developmental testing. Continue program office management and administration process to include program
oversight, resource justification, budgeting and programming, milestone, and schedule tracking.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
