B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                        FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
FY 2026 Plans:
FY2026 centrally funds core Platform One (P1) services that enable continuous delivery of software capabilities through secure,
tailorable and agile software factory services, tools, and standards. These services include but are not limited to: software
vulnerability management pipelines and repository dedicated to software Supply Chain Risk Management (SCRM) and Software
Bill of Materials (SBOM) for Commercial and Open Source software; Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tailorable and deployable to
unclassified and classified operational environments; real-time security implementation and monitoring that expedites the initial
and routine compliance assessments of the Risk Management Framework (RMF). FY2026 focus areas include, but not limited to:

- Integrate data feeds informing assessments of software within Iron Bank to increase software supply chain insights across the
Department of War (DoW) and Defense Industry Base (DIB).

- Develop additional distributions of the Big Bang platform to proliferate simplified deployments tailored to Artificial Intelligence/
Machine Learning (AI/ML), Data Operations (DataOps), and other emerging use cases.

- Develop, integrate, and deliver increased automation and self-service options within the Big Bang platform available to all
downstream consumers.

- Integrate and operate collaboration tools for software development and operational communities.

- Onboard new DevSecOps solutions, tools, and vendors to the pre-evaluated Marketplace to reduce acquisition timelines across
the DoW.

In addition, FY2026 funds inflationary costs associated with P1 Development, Security, and Operations labor contracts.
FY 2027 Plans:
FY2027 will centrally fund core P1 services that will enable continuous delivery of software capabilities through secure, tailorable
